<topic id="ch_css_selectors">
  <title>CSS Selectors</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>CSS selectors</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>CSS selectors are used to target elements in an XML document in order to style them. There
      are a wide variety of CSS selectors available, allowing for fine-grained precision when
      selecting elements to style.</p>
    <p id="p_wtv_dgk_54b">The following table summarizes the selectors supported by <ph
        keyref="product"/>:<table id="table_nnv_mpt_cbb" frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
        <tgroup cols="4">
          <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth="2.25*"/>
          <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth="9.01*"/>
          <colspec colnum="3" colname="col3" colwidth="3.14*"/>
          <colspec colnum="4" colname="col4" colwidth="1*" align="center"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Pattern</entry>
              <entry>Meaning</entry>
              <entry>Described in section</entry>
              <entry>CSS level</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>*</entry>
              <entry>Any element</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#universal-selector"
                  format="html" scope="external">Universal selector</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E</entry>
              <entry>An element of type E</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#type-selectors" format="html"
                  scope="external">Type selector</xref></entry>
              <entry>1</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element with the <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                set</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo="bar"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                value is exactly "bar"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo~="bar"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                value is a list of space-separated values, one of which is exactly equal to
                "bar"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo^="bar"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                value begins exactly with the string "bar"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>3</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo$="bar"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                value ends exactly with the string "bar"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>3</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[foo*="bar"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>foo</xmlatt> attribute
                value contains the substring "bar"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>3</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E[lang|="en"]</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>lang</xmlatt> attribute has
                a hyphen-separated list of values beginning (from the left) with "en"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#attribute-selectors"
                  format="html" scope="external">Attribute selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>2</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E.myclass</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>class</xmlatt> is equal to
                "myclass"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#class-html" format="html"
                  scope="external">Class selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>1</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>E#myid</entry>
              <entry>An <xmlelement>E</xmlelement> element whose <xmlatt>id</xmlatt> is equal to
                "myid"</entry>
              <entry><xref href="https://www.w3.org/TR/selectors-3/#id-selectors" format="html"
                  scope="external">ID selectors</xref></entry>
              <entry>1</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table></p>
